The paper discusses the use of biological neural networks to improve machine learning performance, specifically in the low-data regime. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning methods such as neural nets, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of the insect olfactory network for image recognition tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the AL-MB network as a feature generator, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential deployment of the AL-MB network in deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
